The paper deals with the computational geometry problem of maintaining and updating Voronoi diagrams, which is a classic topic in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents a data structure that maintains the Voronoi diagram, which involves designing efficient algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the combinatorial changes needed to update the Voronoi diagram, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also presents a semi-dynamic data structure that maintains the Voronoi diagram of a set of sites, which involves control theory and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the graph structure of the Voronoi diagram, which falls under cs.GR (Graphics).
